### **ğŸ“Œ Summary of Inter-VLAN Blocking ACL**  

âœ… **Purpose:** Prevents communication between **VLAN1 (192.168.1.0/24)** and **VLAN2 (192.168.2.0/24)** while allowing all other traffic.  

| Rule | Action | Source | Destination | Effect |
|------|--------|--------|-------------|--------|
| 1ï¸âƒ£ | `deny` | `192.168.1.0/24` | `192.168.2.0/24` | **Blocks VLAN1 â†’ VLAN2** |
| 2ï¸âƒ£ | `deny` | `192.168.2.0/24` | `192.168.1.0/24` | **Blocks VLAN2 â†’ VLAN1** |
| 3ï¸âƒ£ | `permit` | `any` | `any` | **Allows all other traffic (e.g., Internet)** |

âœ… **Prevents VLAN1 & VLAN2 from direct communication**  
âœ… **Ensures VLANs can still access external networks (Internet)**  
âœ… **Explicit `permit ip any any` prevents an implicit deny**  

